,Recommended,246940,8891256,"Posted: 28 January, 2014",all,Xi Jinping's Island Vacations,"This game was a bit weird when I first started playing it, and there are some issues with overly long build times that break the sense of a dynamic economic structure and civilization. There are also issues with colony building, wherein buildings would take forever to build, due to the planet's low level of development, even given that these were basic structures designed to boost development and production rates, causing a reciporicating cycle of being unable to have more productive planets, but being tied up in the process of making them more productive, whilst trying to build other things, which interrupts development. This said, the game has a lot of depth, even in early access, and seems to have very good custimization options. Also, the research tree looks good, from what little gameplay I've experienced, though it could be expanded, as it is relatively short. All of these flaws are easily fixable in development, and seeing as this is early access, I'm confident the necessary improvements will be made. All in all, it is a promising, if currently immature title which deserves your consideration, especially given the reasonable price."
