,Recommended,246940,33649067,Posted: 19 July,all,JolanXBL,"Hasn't crashed on me yet.As with all space strategy games, it comes to a point where it's just a slog - dealing with one civilization after another. Spent my 5 hours on building trade routes and being mr. nice potato to everyone I met. Have to play it multiple times to see what strategy will push you to a resolution, I played 2 incomplete rounds in the 5.1 hours as of this review.First round, I didn't make any Colony ships so really only had the one planet.Second round, I expanded to 5 areas, made 5 friends, Allied with 1, declared war on another.. but then I was deep into the slog.I think Production only has to do with the planet it's on, whereas Research adds across your empire. The number of factories you can build depends on the 'Resources' of the planet, so often you can make 2 Factories, then all Research. Demolish later to add banking, police and whatever else you unlock, depending on the planet's purpose. What I should have built more of were shipyards as it took 11 turns to get anything from my Home to the front lines.Research Tree is pretty vast; it's split into 3 categories - Science, Economics, Military. Spent most of my research on Economics to get the gravy flowing, then some into Science to help later research. Military I only touched for the engines, really. But if you focus on Economics, then you should finish with them as progress will just slog while you get your weapons up to snuff.Menus are pretty self-explainatory. You have a handshake for diplomacy, eye for intelligence, ship-with-arrow for next ship.. stuff like that. You only have to click on them once or twice to see what they do. Only issue I had with that is the Tutorial's (descriptive boxes) font is really small.Navigational plane is 2-d, and I haven't touched on battles yet. Ships have a preset shape; the 'building' part is just placing different parts into their respective slots so kinda disappointed about that honestly.Conclusion: Currently it's marked as 32.99 CAD and for that price.. HELLLLLLLL No. I got it on a Steam sale for a really good price so in my opinion 10.00 is the most I'd pay... but when it comes to a Steam Sale, I can still be El Cheapo :P."
